description:
This morning, I received a marketing email from Cloudflare (through one of our mailing groups), being militant about these kinds of emails, I immediately go to unsubscribe.<p>Dark pattern one: You must login to manage your marketing preferences. There's no security related emails here, so this is completely unnecessary.<p>Dark pattern two: &quot;...confirm your email address to save your communication preferences.&quot;. I've no idea how we have a several-year old account without a confirmed email, but it should not have to confirm an email to remove old marketing preferences - or if cloudflare is so careful about this, why did it end up opted-in ion the first place?<p>Dark pattern two-point-five is that the email somehow became unverified - something it seems is only necessary to adjust marketing emails.<p>Okay, so I hit the &quot;Resend verification email&quot; link and check my inbox, nothing just yet. I wait a little longer. It's odd that I immediately got a security email about the login from a new IP, but I've not received this verification email yet.<p>10 minutes later, and I've still not got anything. I know these things <i>can</i> take longer, but I don't have the patience, especially since Cloudflare are clearly trying to make this hard.<p>Going to the preferences page, I hit that verify link again - still nothing. Okay, F12, I switch to the network inspector and click the link <i>again</i>.<p>To my surprise: Absolutely nothing. There's no network requests being initiated by this link. Maybe it's websockets, or maybe there's a script that failed to load? The UI does respond when I hit the link, but nothing else. I opened up the element inspector to find a click handler:<p><pre><code>  function () {
      return a.setState({
          toast: 'verificationResent'
      })
  }

</code></pre>
That is certainly less than I was expecting. If that's just a react setState... this link is literally doing nothing other changing the UI when I press it. Perhaps some silly frontend developer reads that `toast` state elsewhere to trigger the real behaviour? Nope the only other reference to verificationResent is a ternary statement in the render function.<p>Dark pattern three: Just break unsubscribe. The cynic in me says this was intentional. Hanlon's razor tells me perhaps it is just a mistake, in which case dark pattern three is the overengineering of the unsubscribe function so you can get as much dropoff as possible and it's most convenient if it just breaks.<p>So wtf Cloudflare?<p>Oh, and to supplement dark pattern two: The verification check is only on the frontend. In the end, I was able to use the debugger to skip the verified check and edit &amp; submit my email preferences anyway.

description_zh-Hans:
今天早上，我收到了一封来自Cloudflare的营销邮件（通过我们的一个邮件组），对这类邮件很好战，我立即去取消了订阅。<p>黑暗模式一。你必须登录以管理你的营销偏好。这里没有与安全有关的电子邮件，所以这完全没有必要。<p>黑暗模式二：&quot;...确认您的电子邮件地址以保存您的通信偏好。I've no idea how we have a several-year old account without a confirmed email, but it should not have to confirm an email to remove old marketing preferences - or if cloudflare is so careful about this, why did it end up opted-in ion the first place?<p>Dark pattern two-point-five is that the email somehow became unverified - something it seems is only necessary to adjust marketing emails.<p>Okay, so I hit the &quot;Resend verification email&quot; link and check my inbox, nothing just yet. I wait a little longer. It's odd that I immediately got a security email about the login from a new IP, but I've not received this verification email yet.<p>10 minutes later, and I've still not got anything. I know these things <i>can</i> take longer, but I don't have the patience, especially since Cloudflare are clearly trying to make this hard.<p>Going to the preferences page, I hit that verify link again - still nothing. Okay, F12, I switch to the network inspector and click the link <i>again</i>.<p>To my surprise: Absolutely nothing. There's no network requests being initiated by this link. 也许是网络套接字，或者是有一个脚本未能加载？当我点击这个链接时，用户界面确实有反应，但没有其他反应。我打开元素检查器，找到一个点击处理程序：<p><pre><code> function () {
      return a.setState({
          toast: 'verificationResent
      })
  }

</code></pre>
That is certainly less than I was expecting. 如果这只是一个反应式的setState......这个链接除了在我按下它的时候改变UI之外，实际上什么也没做。也许一些愚蠢的前端开发者从其他地方读取了 "toast "状态来触发真正的行为？没有，唯一提到verificationResent的是渲染函数中的一个三元组语句。<p>黑暗模式三。只是破坏了退订。我这个愤世嫉俗的人说这是故意的。汉伦剃刀告诉我，也许这只是一个错误，在这种情况下，黑暗模式三是过度设计退订功能，所以你可以得到尽可能多的下降，如果它只是打破了，那是最方便的。<p>那么，什么是Cloudflare？<p>哦，为了补充黑暗模式二。验证检查只在前台进行。最后，我能够使用调试器跳过验证检查并编辑&amp;提交我的电子邮件偏好。

description_zh-Hant:
今天早上，我收到了一封來自Cloudflare的營銷郵件（通過我們的一個郵件組），對這類郵件很好戰，我立即去取消了訂閱。<p>黑暗模式一。你必須登錄以管理你的營銷偏好。這裡沒有與安全有關的電子郵件，所以這完全沒有必要。<p>黑暗模式二：&quot;...確認您的電子郵件地址以保存您的通信偏好。I've no idea how we have a several-year old account without a confirmed email, but it should not have to confirm an email to remove old marketing preferences - or if cloudflare is so careful about this, why did it end up opted-in ion the first place?<p>Dark pattern two-point-five is that the email somehow became unverified - something it seems is only necessary to adjust marketing emails.<p>Okay, so I hit the &quot;Resend verification email&quot; link and check my inbox, nothing just yet. I wait a little longer. It's odd that I immediately got a security email about the login from a new IP, but I've not received this verification email yet.<p>10 minutes later, and I've still not got anything. I know these things <i>can</i> take longer, but I don't have the patience, especially since Cloudflare are clearly trying to make this hard.<p>Going to the preferences page, I hit that verify link again - still nothing. Okay, F12, I switch to the network inspector and click the link <i>again</i>.<p>To my surprise: Absolutely nothing. There's no network requests being initiated by this link. 也許是網絡套接字，或者是有一個腳本未能加載？當我點擊這個鏈接時，用戶界面確實有反應，但沒有其他反應。我打開元素檢查器，找到一個點擊處理程序：<p><pre><code> function () {
      return a.setState({
          toast: 'verificationResent
      })
  }

</code></pre>
That is certainly less than I was expecting. 如果這只是一個反應式的setState......這個鏈接除了在我按下它的時候改變UI之外，實際上什麼也沒做。也許一些愚蠢的前端開發者從其他地方讀取了 "toast "狀態來觸發真正的行為？沒有，唯一提到verificationResent的是渲染函數中的一個三元組語句。<p>黑暗模式三。只是破壞了退訂。我這個憤世嫉俗的人說這是故意的。漢倫剃刀告訴我，也許這只是一個錯誤，在這種情況下，黑暗模式三是過度設計退訂功能，所以你可以得到儘可能多的下降，如果它只是打破了，那是最方便的。<p>那麼，什麼是Cloudflare？<p>哦，為了補充黑暗模式二。驗證檢查只在前臺進行。最後，我能夠使用調試器跳過驗證檢查並編輯&amp;提交我的電子郵件偏好。
